<h2><a href="/2008/04/15/postcards.from.hereabouts" title="Permanent link to this item">Postcards from hereabouts</a></h2>

<h3><span class="outleft">15 Apr 2008, 12pm</span></h3>

<p>(Shameless plug ahead, but it’s a good one.)</p>
<p>Our friends Ruth and Julian live over on the other side of the Rhône, in hardcore garlic-and-tomatoes Provence, right at the foot of the inescapable <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mont_Ventoux" title="Wikipedia entry on a big hill">Mont Ventoux</a>. Despite preferring cats over dogs they’re good people; less, you know, <em>English</em> than a lot of the expats who live down here. She’s an accomplished <a href="http://ruthphillips.com/">cellist </a>(as far as I’m aware the only person I know to have played on a Portishead album) and he’s a painter. We’ve been playing dinner party tennis for a few years now, which is always good loud fun.</p>
<p><span class="outright">Nice <em>NY Times</em> piece on Julian’s work <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/slideshow/2006/02/22/garden/20060223_CURR_SLIDESHOW_1.html">here</a>.</span></p>
<p>Anyway for the past couple years Julian, while doing larger commissioned work, has also been painting little gems – ‘Postcards from Provence’ – every day and putting them for sale <a href="http://shiftinglight.com">on his site</a>. At first they went for $100 a pop, and would always be snapped up a few seconds after appearing. Then, in the past year or so, the paintings have been up for auction on a mini-ebayish application that may or may not have been built by me.</p>
<p>You really do want to have one of these small treasures in your home. <a href="http://auction.shiftinglight.com">I direct you there at once</a>. Bid strong and bid often. Transactions are via PayPal, and he ships worldwide for Iike peanuts. Go! <em>Go!</em></p>
